booking.info:
All San Francisco Health Network patients age 16 and older can book appointments or check availability.

Drop in hours are 9 am to 3 pm daily. First doses only — second doses are scheduled onsite when you get your first.

remote_translation.info: More languages via live phone interpreters

open_to.text:
Appointments open to all San Francisco Health Network patients age 16 and older.

Drop-ins open to any of:
  • San Francisco Health Network patients age 16 and older
  • All residents age 16 and over living the following zip codes: 94124, 94134, 94107, 94110, 94112, 94102, 94103, and 94130
  • All SF residents age 65 and older
  • Anyone age 16 and over with HealthySF insurance
  • In-home support service providers
  • Uninsured SF residents age 16 and over

This site often has Pfizer, the only vaccine available for people age 16 and 17. People under 18 need to be accompanied by a parent or guardian to be vaccinated. Please confirm that they will have Pfizer when you book.
